Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Software Engineer & Reporting Administrator* role with *Benedict College*. I bring over three years of software engineering experience and an MS in Computer Science from Pace University, with a track record of building reliable systems that balance long-term ownership with day-to-day user support.

In my current Software Engineer role at Sperse, I own systems across the full lifecycle—*requirements gathering*, implementation, deployment, and maintenance. I built an MCP interaction layer that translates natural-language requests into safe, validated tool calls across *1000+ platform endpoints*, and I developed integration accelerators that standardized *REST APIs* for internal *reporting systems* and *work order tickets*. Previously at Qualitest, I built a support chatbot with LangChain, RAG, and PostgreSQL that reduced average ticket resolution time by *20%*, and I contributed to an IAM platform supporting thousands of users across *30+ applications* with React, Spring Boot, and AWS. This mix of ownership, troubleshooting, and cross-team communication aligns directly with your need for someone who can design, deploy, and steward campus software with strong customer service.

I am especially drawn to Benedict College’s mission of delivering *transformative learning experiences* through quality programming for a diverse student body. Your emphasis on *innovation*, *customer service*, and *community engagement* strongly matches how I work. As an AI Researcher at Pace AI Lab, I delivered full model lifecycle work with CUDA, PyTorch, and LoRA, and I mentored *50+* students through workshops on GPU programming and AI agent engineering—experience that maps well to the communication and mentorship expectations in this role, including supporting interns and partnering with non-technical stakeholders.

I would be honored to contribute to Benedict College’s goal of preparing students with strong cultural and professional competencies for the global marketplace. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration.

